     PRELIMINARY DATES SET FOR 1995 RSA DATA SECURITY CONFERENCE

     We are publicly posting these dates in order to avoid conflicts with 
     other planned events in the security/crypto/privacy community; PLEASE 
     NOTIFY US IMMEDIATLEY IF YOU KNOW OF ANY MAJOR SECURITY-RELATED EVENT 
     CONFLICTING WITH THE PLANNED DATES OF OUR CONFERENCE. 

     Send Comments and notices to kurt@rsa.com

     **************************************************

     RSA Data Security is pleased to announce our fourth annual RSA Data 
     Security Conference, to be held at the Hotel Sofitel in Redwood 
     Shores, California. The conference is set for Monday, Tuesday and 
     Wednesday January 9, 10 and 11, 1995.

     Included will be presentations and products from RSA's major licensees, 
     including Apple, Microsoft, Novell, Lotus and many others... Panel 
     discussions from experts from government and industry... Tutorials 
     going all the way from the basics to advanced crypto theory and
     application.  

     Registration is limited to 450 people and will begin in late August; 
     watch this newsgroup for an official notification. Registration fee is 
     $295.

     Conference Dates:
     January 9th, 10th and 11th, 1995.

     Registration Deadline:
     Friday, December 16, 1994.
     THERE WILL BE NO REGISTRATION AT THE DOOR. 

     Registration fee includes 
     * breakfast and lunch all three days
     * admission to the conference and all tutorials 
     * a hardcopy of the full conference proceedings 
     * two cocktail receptions
     * and the coveted 1995 RSA conference souvenir. 

     Cancellations are subject to a $50 administrative fee.

     Travel Information:

     Hotel Sofitel 
     Guaranteed rate $103 per night for conference attendees, 
     call (415) 598-9000 The Hotel Sofitel offers a complimentary
     shuttle from the San Francisco airport, just ten minutes away.

